Type: Project
Package: data-science-for-biologists-az
Title: R for Biologists — Data Science, Bioinformatics, Machine Learning, and Omics Analysis in R
Version: 1.0.0
Description: A complete R curriculum for biologists and bioinformaticians covering data wrangling,
    visualization, statistical reasoning, tidymodels-based machine learning, omics analysis with
    limma, survival analysis with Cox models and penalized regression, and reproducible research
    with renv and R Markdown. Uses real clinical and microarray expression data throughout.
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1)
Imports:
    broom,
    glmnet,
    here,
    limma,
    pheatmap,
    ranger,
    renv,
    scales,
    survival,
    survminer,
    themis,
    tidymodels,
    tidyverse,
    vip
